-- Cuba's Castro says he will attend Americas summit
-- By Daniel Trotta
-- Sat Dec 20, 2014 11:07AM EST
-- None



HAVANA, Dec 20 (Reuters) - Cuban President Raul Castro confirmed on Saturday he will participate in the Washington-backed Summit of the Americas in Panama in April, potentially setting up his first meeting with U.S. President Barack Obama since the two countries agreed on Wednesday to reestablish diplomatic ties.   (Reporting by Daniel Trotta; Editing by Mark Trevelyan)  ((daniel.trotta@reuters.com; +537 833 3145; Reuters Messaging: daniel.trotta@thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: CUBA USA/SUMMIT

